# Copy this file to ".env" and paste at least one key. The app auto-detects which you
# have and ROTATES across them (priority: Groq -> Gemini -> Claude): if one hits its
# free-tier limit, it automatically switches to the next.
# TIP: add several keys to one provider by comma-separating them, e.g.
#   GROQ_API_KEY=key_from_account1,key_from_account2
#
# Option A — Groq (FREE, fast, generous limits — recommended):
#   Get a key at: https://console.groq.com/keys
GROQ_API_KEY=your-groq-key-here
#
# Option B — Google Gemini (free tier, small daily quota):
#   Get a key at: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
# GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-key-here
#
# Option C — Anthropic Claude (paid credits):
#   Get a key at: https://console.anthropic.com  (Settings -> API Keys)
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=sk-ant-your-key-here
#
# The retrieval part works WITHOUT any key; you only need it for AI answers,
# quizzes, flashcards, cheat-sheets and grading.
#
# Sign JWT login tokens. Use a long random string in production
# (e.g. `python -c "import secrets;print(secrets.token_urlsafe(32))"`).
SECRET_KEY=change-me-to-a-long-random-string
